default2. defaultThe defaulthdefaultomeopathic defaultadefaultpproachdefaultHomeopaths often see patients 
defaultafter they have received a medical diagnosis from their doctor and many of these patients have 
defaultlong-term
default health
default 
defaultproblems that 
defaultfail to respond to conventional medicine. 
defaultSome individuals seek a homeopath because they are experiencing side effects from conventional drugs and others because conventional tests have failed to find the cause of their problem. 
defaultAs a system of medicine, homeopathy aim
defaults to treat patients as whole people
default, rather than 
defaultfocusing on a course of action for each 
defaultdisease diagnosis
default, thus
default offering a different approach
default. A
defaults such
default, homeopathic treatment
default can be considered 
defaultas a supportive option 
defaultin almost any 
defaultcondition
default where tissue has not been irrevocably damaged.
default Homeopaths working according to the Society’s code of ethics 
defaultencourage
default their patients 
defaultto keep 
defaulttheir appropriate
default 
defaultmedical practitioners informed when they seek homeopathic treatment and as treatment progresses. When necessary homeopathic and conventional approaches can be used alongside one another to give the most appropriate care
default to each individual patient, thus integrating all medical approaches and adjunctive advice the patient has been given to manage their health.
default3. defaultWhat is homeopathy?defaultThe 
defaultMeSH
default 
defaultdefinition of homeopathy 
defaultis
default:
default“A system of therapeutics founded by Samuel Hahnemann (1755-1843), based on the Law of Similars where ‘like cures like’. Diseases are treated by highly diluted substances that cause, in healthy persons, symptoms like those to be treated. The dilutions are repeated so many times that there is less than one molecule per dose and it is suggested that benefit is from the energetic life force of the original substance”
default.
defaultH
defaultomeop
defaultathy 
defaultcan therefore be seen as 
defaulta 
default‘
defaultholistic
default’
default therapy
default, such that homeopathic care 
defaulttakes into account all aspects of th
defaulte 
defaultpatient as an 
defaultindividual 
defaultassessing 
defaulttheir symptoms
default on 
defaultmental, emotional, physical and general
default levels
default. 
defaultDuring a consultation the professional homeopath
default 
defaultwill focus
default on building up a complete picture of 
defaultan 
defaultindividual’s unique make up considering all aspects of the patient’s health including diet, medical history, 
defaultlife events, 
defaultlifestyle and personality. 
defaultHomeopathic p
defaultrescription
defaults are
default based on the 
defaultprocess of 
defaultmatching this unique collection of symptoms 
defaultas closely as possible 
defaultwith
default those of an appropriate 
defaulthomeopathic medicine (called a ‘
defaultremedy
default’), rather than automatically prescribing the same medicine for a named 
defaultcondition. This 
defaultapproach to understanding patients’ cases 
defaultmakes homeopathy well placed to treat those people with a diversity of complaints 
defaultthat
default would 
defaultconventionally 
defaultbe given a different medication for each condition. For example
default,
default a 
defaultperson
default with asthma
default, allergies and constipation would typically
default require thre
