default1default2default. defaultCost effectivenessdefaultCost effectiveness studies indicate 
defaultthat
default the use 
defaultof homeopathy as a treatment option can reduce financial burden on patients and healthcare providers alike. 
defaultIn Europe, a Health Technology Assessment of homeopathy commissioned by the Swiss government recently concluded that homeopathy is “clinically effective, cost effective and safe” (
defaultBornhöft
default et al.
default, 2006). 
defaultAdditionally
default, a comparison of homeopathic and conventional treatment of 493 patients with chronic conditions in Germany found that homeopathy achieved better outcomes for similar costs (Witt 
defaultet al., 
default2005) and 
defaulta study involving 499 ch
defaultildren 
defaultwith recurrent upper respiratory tract infections showed that 
defaulthomeopathic treatment was more clinically effective 
default(fewer episodes of illness) 
defaultand 
defaultmore 
defaultcost
default-effective than antibiotics (
defaultTri
defaultchard
default et al.
default, 2005).
default 
